## Storage Layer

File: `storage/task-storage.ts`

Tasks are stored per-user. The storage key includes the userId so two users on the same device never share tasks.

```ts
import AsyncStorage from '@react-native-async-storage/async-storage';
import { Task } from '@/types/task';

const storageKey = (userId: string) => `TASK_TRACKER_TASKS_${userId}`;

export const loadTasks = async (userId: string): Promise<Task[]> => {
  try {
    const data = await AsyncStorage.getItem(storageKey(userId));
    return data ? JSON.parse(data) : [];
  } catch {
    return [];
  }
};

export const saveTasks = async (userId: string, tasks: Task[]): Promise<void> => {
  try {
    await AsyncStorage.setItem(storageKey(userId), JSON.stringify(tasks));
  } catch {}
};
```

Rules:
- Always include `userId` in the storage key
- Always JSON.stringify on save
- Always JSON.parse on load
- Always wrap in try/catch
- Never throw from storage functions

