## Navigation

Four screens, in order of flow:

1. `WalkthroughScreen` — shown once on first launch only. On CTA press, mark walkthrough seen and redirect to `/(auth)/login`.
2. `LoginScreen` — email + password form. On success, set user in UserContext and redirect to `/(tabs)`.
3. `SignupScreen` — name + email + password form. On success, set user and redirect to `/(tabs)`.
4. `HomeScreen` — main app screen.

Redirect logic in `app/index.tsx`:
- Has not seen walkthrough → `/(onboarding)/walkthrough`
- Has seen walkthrough, no user → `/(auth)/login`
- Has user → `/(tabs)`

Track first launch with `hooks/use-onboarding.ts` using AsyncStorage key `HAS_SEEN_WALKTHROUGH`.
Track auth state via `UserContext` — user is `null` when logged out.

Auth is local/mock for this project (no backend). Login stores the user object in AsyncStorage under key `AUTH_USER` and loads it on app start via `UserState`.

