## README Requirements

The repository README must include these sections exactly:

### Project Overview

One paragraph describing the app. Example:

> Task Tracker is a React Native mobile app built with Expo and TypeScript. It lets users create, manage, and filter tasks that persist locally across sessions.

### Setup Instructions

```md
## Setup

1. Clone the repository
   git clone <repo-url>
   cd task-tracker-rn

2. Install dependencies
   npm install

3. Start the app
   npx expo start

Scan the QR code with Expo Go (iOS or Android) or press `i` for iOS simulator / `a` for Android emulator.
```

### Libraries Used and Why

```md
## Libraries

| Library | Why |
|---|---|
| expo-router | File-based routing — keeps navigation declarative and co-located with screens |
| @react-native-async-storage/async-storage | Simple key-value local persistence for tasks and auth session |
| nativewind | Tailwind CSS in React Native — consistent, readable styling without StyleSheet boilerplate |
| expo-splash-screen | Holds the splash screen while auth session is restored on startup |
| react-native-safe-area-context | Correct inset handling for notch and home indicator on all devices |
| clsx + tailwind-merge | Conditional className composition without conflicts |
```

